               "text": "### Images from ESA\n\nThese images are copyright for ESA and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgESA2\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgESA2', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Planck history of Universe. ©ESA – C. Carreau (<htcite0>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Atlas: Everything Together - An initial explanation of the period when matter and energy were united. (<htcite2>)</li><li>Atlas: The Origin of the Universe - Our current understanding of the evolution of the universe and the view people had of it millennia ago. (<htcite3>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: Limits and contexts - a common point between science and writing is the fact that people do not always understand their limits. But how can we identify them? (<htcite4>)</li><li>Mathematical Games: Building to count (Suanpan, 算盤) - In this text, we see the differences and what is in common between the Chinese abacus and the Japanese abacus. (<htcite5>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: Is the universe static? - In this text, we take a journey back in time to understand what current measurements reveal about the universe’s past. (<htcite6>)</li><li>Physics: Evolution of Knowledge: The Atom - In this text, we study how our idea of the atom has evolved over time. (<htcite13>)</li><li>Physics: Expanding... - Continuing from the previous text, we see that dividing into just two sides ends up doing omissions (<htcite9>)</li><li>Physics: Together we are strong - In this text, we see how the four operations, when combined, open the doors to so much knowledge (<htcite10>)</li><li>Physics: Two sides - good vs. evil, left vs. right, matter vs. energy, up vs. down. Is this duality enough? (<htcite12>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgESA1\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgESA1', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">View of the Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB) through the ESA Planck mission. ©ESA/Planck Collaboration (<htcite1>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Atlas: Cosmic Microwave Background - An explanation of how the Cosmic Microwave Background helped confirm the Big Bang theory. (<htcite7>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: Is it possible to live in the sky? Is the Earth flat? - <p>Our knowledge in different fields has developed over time. In ancient times, the scattering of light in the atmosphere was mistaken for the sky itself. Since going beyond the atmosphere was unimaginable, human thought projected the possibility of building something to reach the 'sky' or even to live in it. After millennia of study, we know that ancient texts reflected the knowledge of their time or, at best, were metaphorical writings.</p><p>Similarly, the shape of the Earth was also unknown in antiquity. It was only in <htdate0> that the Earth’s sphericity was demonstrated. Even so, due to certain fictions, some people returned to believing it might be flat. Additional details can be found in the <i>Atlas</i> section (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('f140d8d6-80cc-4d82-b9f7-c3ba06bf2ed3'); return false;\">History Tracers Team, <htdate1>, Atlas</a>).</p> (<htcite8>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: Is the universe static? - In this text, we take a journey back in time to understand what current measurements reveal about the universe’s past. (<htcite6>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">3 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgUniverseTimeBigBang\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgUniverseTimeBigBang', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\"></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">4 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgWebbDisc\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgWebbDisc', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\"></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">5 / 5</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgGaiaStarFormation\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgGaiaStarFormation', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\"></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
